ZH: 这座城墙已有千年的历史。
EN: This city wall has a history of a thousand years.

ZH: 城墙上留下了许多历史的印记。
EN: The city wall bears many traces of history.

ZH: 昨天我在城墙上散步。
EN: I took a walk on the city wall yesterday.

ZH: 这座城墙的设计非常精美。
EN: The design of this city wall is very exquisite.

ZH: 每天都有很多游客来参观这座城墙。
EN: Many tourists come to visit this city wall every day.

ZH: 沿着城墙散步能看到整座城市的全貌。
EN: Walking along the city wall gives a panoramic view of the whole city.

ZH: 城墙被很多青藤覆盖着。
EN: The city wall is covered with a lot of ivy.

ZH: 警卫沿着城墙巡逻。
EN: Guards patrol along the city wall.

ZH: 历史上，城墙曾经是防御的重要工事。
EN: In history, city walls used to be important defense structures.

ZH: 这座城墙现在用来保护古城。
EN: This city wall is now used to protect the old town.

ZH: 夕阳下，城墙显得格外壮丽。
EN: Under the setting sun, the city wall looks especially magnificent.

ZH: 草坪旁边是一道古老的城墙。
EN: Next to the lawn is an ancient city wall.

ZH: 城墙上的钟楼已经历史悠久。
EN: The clock tower on the city wall has a long history.

ZH: 沿着城墙边走，仿佛穿越了时光。
EN: Walking along the edge of the city wall feels like traveling through time.

ZH: 城墙上镶嵌着许多美丽的瓷砖。
EN: The city wall is adorned with many beautiful tiles.

ZH: 在城墙上可以俯瞰整个城市。
EN: From the city wall, you can overlook the entire city.

ZH: 建造这座城墙耗费了大量的人力物力。
EN: Building this city wall required a lot of human and material resources.

ZH: 这段城墙已经修葺了很多次。
EN: This section of the city wall has been repaired many times.

ZH: 砖砌的城墙结构十分坚固。
EN: The brick-built city wall structure is very sturdy.

ZH: 很多游客都被这座城墙的历史吸引。
EN: Many tourists are drawn to the history of this city wall.
